<topic id="performance-problems-external-processes">
  <title>External Processes</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Out Of Memory error</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The <xref
        href="preferences-fo-processors.dita#preferences-fo-processors/memory-available-fop"
          ><uicontrol>Memory available to the built-in FOP</uicontrol> option</xref> controls the
      amount of memory allocated to generate PDF output with the built-in Apache FOP processor. If
          <ph><ph keyref="product"/></ph> throws an <i>Out Of Memory</i> error, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol> XML</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> XSLT-FO-XQuery</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> FO Processors</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>, and increase the value of the <xref
        href="preferences-fo-processors.dita#preferences-fo-processors/memory-available-fop"
          ><uicontrol>Memory available to the built-in FOP</uicontrol> option</xref>.</p>
    <p>For external XSL-FO processors, XSLT processors, and external tools, the maximum value of the
      allocated memory is set in the command line of the tool using the <parmname>-Xmx</parmname>
      parameter set to the Java virtual machine. </p>
  </body>
